Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Lexicographical & Linguistic Studies
Author: BURCHFIELD
Vol / Page: 191
Edition:
Quote: aroha /|aroha/. N.Z. [Maori, cogn. w. Hawaiian  aloha.] Affection, love; sympathy.  In Hawaii the phoneme /l/ was sometimes perceived in the late 18c. and the early 19c. as /r/. Hawaiian examples of aloha are not given below.
Notes:

